Earlier this month, I had the opportunity to be in front of the camera with an iconic group of women who, with the help of NYC-based organization, Custom Collaborative (@customcolab), were able to learn and execute a new skill set in sustainable fashion. @CustomColab envisions a world in which all women possess the skills, confidence, and agency to design their futures and contribute to a  sustainable world — regardless of race or socio-economic background.
I’m so proud of this photoshoot, by the incredible Camila Falquez, which has been featured in Vogue Business for serving as the blueprint for what a sustainable, inclusive fashion industry can look like. 
Since getting to know their talent and seeing their mission in action, I’ve volunteered to raise funds for their innovative programs. I hope you’ll consider supporting Custom Collaborative’s year-end campaign, by making a donation today. Together, we can achieve their $50,000 goal by December 31st.

During NYFW I attended Remake’s Week "Party With a Purpose" with Mara Hoffman in celebration of The FABRIC Act — an initiative that’ll protect and ensure garment workers a livable wage. 

This billion dollar fashion industry that we flock to NY to celebrate twice per year, is literally upheld by thousands highly skilled garment workers who, even in 2023, are still making under $3/hr for extremely long working days and harsh working conditions. This NYFW it’s bigger than just clothes, we’re pushing for a fashion industry that maintains its integrity and ethics at every level. 

Go to thefabricact.org and @remakeourworld for more info  #PassFABRICAct 🌍

🤍 Wearing a completely up-cycled look by @theobot @ab.adprojects 🤍

I know I’m late lol but did you catch my comeback to @projectrunwaybravo for the Season 20 All Stars Finale?!

Well to be fully transparent, filming this episode was bitter sweet for me. Sweet because we filmed on my birthday (11/11) and it felt great to see some old faces, meet some new ones, and prepare to hit the runway. Bitter because while filming, during hair & makeup, I found out that my great grandmother, Rosa Lee Shorters, had passed away at 101 years young.

So as much as I’d like to talk about how much fun I was having and how beautifully chaotic and invigorating my experience was, I think it’s more important to speak about the reason why this day was particularly special to me. 

My Grandma Rose had no problem letting the world know that my beauty and all of the beauty in our family came from her, her bloodline— and she was the prettiest of us all. While I took a moment to pull myself together backstage, I reminded myself whose blood is running through me. Blood of a woman who lived 101 years gracefully, confidently, and boldly. I know I carried her energy with me that day. I felt it to the core of my heart and with every single step I took on that runway. 

A month later, we lost my other great Grandma Dot, who marched with Dr. Martin Luther King in Montgomery, AL and whose prayers have sustained our family for generations. It’s the legacy of these two women that I carry with me not just this day, but all the time. 

Rest peacefully Grandma Rose & Grandma Dot. I hope I’m making you both so proud 🤍

Huge thank you to @brittanyallen.atx for designing and casting me in your finale collection & to the other models on set for helping me smile so big that I forgot that I was sad 🥹🫶🏾 11:11

As another 11/11 came around the corner, I realized that even as a kid, I knew self-love was revolutionary. 

I was the late bloomer, a little weird, and was definitely the girl who danced to her own beat. Sometimes I used to wonder if there was something wrong with me for not thinking or behaving like anyone else until I accepted my uniqueness as my superpower. Now I get to be an example of what it looks like when you lean more into your individuality, even when it feels like the world is dragging you in the opposite direction. 

Thank you all for the birthday love & loving on me for me. 13 year old Jazzy is smiling so big right now 🥳 #1111 

Also, thank you to @twodoorsdownnyc_ for the hospitality 🫶🏾
